'''Niefang''' is a city in [[Equatorial Guinea]]. It is located in the province of [[Centro Sur]] and has a (2005 est.) population of 4858. The city was formerly named '''Sevilla de Niefang''' during Spanish occupation. Niefang was traditionally the western border of the [[Fang]] tribal area. Its name means "Limit of the Fang". More to the west were the areas of the coastal Bantu-tribes referred to as "Playeros" (''Beach People'' in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]): [[Combe people|Combes]], [[Bujeba people|Bujebas]], [[Balengue people|Balengues]], and [[Benga people|Bengas]]. Niefang lies on the [[Benito River]].
